Dawn is breaking on independent UK!’ Leave campaigners celebrate historic Brexit victory

2016-06-24

PA

Leave campaigners from  Westminster to Sunderland, some carrying cans of bear and bottles of wine,  waved Union Jacks and Vote Leave banners as they chanted and expressed their joy at the decision.An ecstatic Nigel Farage, leader of eurosceptic Ukip, said: "Dare to dream that the dawn is breaking on an independent United Kingdom. "If the predictions are right this will be a victory for real people, a victory for ordinary people, a victory for decent people. Let June 23 go down in our history as an independence day.“We've got our country back. Thanks to all of you."

PA

On a count floor in Sunderland, where 51,930 voted to remand and 82,394 to leave, there was jubilant scenes as voters clapped and thrust their fists in the air, when it became clear the decision was to leave the EU.On Twitter there was a variety of reactions to the decision to leave the EU.Leave supporter Perdita Hibert wrote: "I'm British and so I won't be celebrating, but I am looking forward to leaving the corrupt, money wasting EU."Brittany Holme tweeted:  "Whatever result you wanted, it's definitely not the time for flag-waving and celebrations. Leaving the EU is a serious decision."

